snippet.textDisplay: The biggest problem I have is I rarely use headphones. I carry wired ones in a small bag with me, but its a once every 2 months things I use them for. removing the headphone jack directly attacked people like me. People that listen to music every day have seen the befit and convenience of wireless buds for how much they cost, but me I have to also carry round this dongle along with my headphones. I haven't got £60 to spend on even the most basic wireless headphones that are going to go flat in my bag after 4 months of not using them. What is amazing how apple basically got it right first time round. the size of the case, the pairing, the charging (eventually improved with wireless). that + samsungs reverse wireless charging it makes them an amazing combination. cant believe they got it so right on a mostly new to the market product.
